1
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:38,316
<i>(crowd shouting)</i>

2
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:08,310
<i>(booing)</i>

3
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:17,431
Come on! Hit 'im! Hit 'im!

4
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:31,436
<i>(bell)</i>

5
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:43,430
You're waltzin'.
Give the sucker some action.

6
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:46,279
You're fightin' like a bum.
Want some advice?

7
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,356
Water!

8
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:52,835
Should I bet the fight
don't go three rounds?

9
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:56,270
- You feel strong?
- Absolutely.

10
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:59,198
You want some good advice?
Keep moving.

11
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,832
<i>(bell)</i>

12
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:07,916
<i>(crowd shouting)</i>

13
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,956
<i>(booing)</i>

14
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:47,151
Give him one!

15
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:59,276
<i>(bell)</i>

16
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:05,590
<i>(cheering and applause)</i>

17
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,394
<i>(bell)</i>

18
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,829
All right, all right!

19
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:23,350
Next a six-rounder
between local lightweights...

20
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:25,516
...Kid Brooks and Sugar Johnson!

21
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,958
- Hey.
- Hey, what?

22
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:42,038
- You got a smoke?
- Yeah, you can have this one.

23
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,676
<i>(man in crowd)</i> You're a bum!

24
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:47,758
You're a bum!
You know that? You're a bum!

25
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:14,677
Hey...

26
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,870
You really got lucky tonight.

27
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:21,118
Spider, you get loser's share:
$40, less $15 locker and cornerman...

28
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:25,756
...$5 shower and towel,
7% tax. Comes to 17.20.

29
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:28,269
You fought a good fight, Spider.

30
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:32,552
Balboa, you get winner's share:
$65, less $15 locker and cornerman...

31
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:35,399
...$5 shower and towel and 7% tax.

32
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:37,875
Comes to 40.55.

33
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:42,679
- When do I fight again?
- Maybe two weeks. Gimme a call.

34
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:45,758
The doctor should be in
in about 20 minutes.

35
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,755
<i>(whistles a tune)</i>

36
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,235
<i>(whistles to dogs)</i>

37
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,475
Here, boy. Here, boy.

38
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,519
# Take you back

39
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:47,915
# Doo doo do-doo, take you back

40
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:51,638
- # Doo doo do-doo
- # I said I've been told by

41
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:55,514
# Doo doo do-doo
Some people and they all

42
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:57,551
# Said take you back

43
00:05:57,680 --> 00:06:01,798
# Doo doo do-doo
Take you back like before

44
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:05,390
# But I don't call it a reason

45
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:09,513
# I just call it believin' in myself

46
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:11,949
# Doo doo do-doo, do-do-doo

47
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,795
# Doo doo do-doo, push me back

48
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:17,957
You guys are gettin' better every year,
you know that?

49
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:20,036
Yeah!

50
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,314
# What I saw before

51
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:29,069
# I squeezed you then I held you

52
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:32,670
# But I could not tell you I loved you

53
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:35,595
# Doo doo do-doo, take you back

54
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,595
- # Doo doo do-doo
- # Well, you put me down

55
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:42,750
# Doo doo do-doo
You put me down real nice

56
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,072
# This love affair

57
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:48,715
# Doo doo do-doo
Is takin' the largest slice

58
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:52,310
# From my life, as I sing...

59
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:31,153
Hey! Your old man
did pretty good tonight.

60
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:35,637
Why weren't you there, huh? You shoulda
seen me. You guys hungry? No?

61
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:40,076
Here you go.

62
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,556
Here you go.

63
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:47,153
You wanna see
your friend Moby Dick, huh?

64
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:53,755
How you doin', Moby Dick?
You miss me today or what, huh?

65
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,557
Huh?

66
00:07:56,680 --> 00:08:02,118
Here you go. Say hi. If you could sing or
dance, I wouldn't be doin' this, you know?

67
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:20,952
And this turtle food I got here, it's uh...

68
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:25,949
This turtle food, gotta add more flies in.
There are more moths in it.

69
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:29,516
More flies... More moths...
Who the hell cares?

70
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:49,154
How you feelin' this mornin'? Full of life?

71
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:52,670
- Fine.
- Hey, how you doin', killer?

72
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:56,236
- How's the turtle food this week?
- Fine.

73
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:59,193
- Me, I'm kinda aggravated, you know?
- Oh, I'm sorry.

74
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:03,677
- Ain't your fault. Wanna hear about it?
- I'll tell you somebody who <i>don't.</i>

75
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,631
How you doin', Gloria?

76
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:09,435
The last turtle food I got here
had more moths in it than flies.

77
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:12,075
The moths get caught
in the turtles' throats.

78
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:16,398
They cough and I smack 'em on the back
of the shell. What do you think they get?

79
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:19,080
And they get what, huh?

80
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:23,874
Come on... Shell-shocked.
They get shell-shocked.

81
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:28,516
- Startin' with the bad jokes early, huh?
- Inventin' jokes ain't so easy sometimes.

82
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,596
- That wasn't a joke.
<i>- (barking)</i>

83
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,029
How's my buddy doin' today? Yo, Butkus!

84
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:35,913
- I ain't had time to check 'im.
- Yo, Butkus!

85
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:40,356
<i>(Rocky howls)</i>

86
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:48,236
Adrian, I want you to go downstairs and
clean all the cat cages. They're a mess.

87
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:04,039
You gotta pay for that
turtle food, Rock-head.

88
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:08,153
Hey, crime don't pay.
You know that, Gloria. You know that.

89
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:32,990
- Yo, Rock, how's your boss?
- Real good.

90
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:35,395
- You fightin' again?
- Yeah, here and there.

91
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:39,229
- We'll make some money real soon, huh?
- Yeah, a million dollars.

92
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,510
Hey, you! Where you goin'?

93
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,838
Where you goin'? Huh?
Where you runnin'?

94
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:51,552
Hey! Hey!

95
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:56,796
- Don't hit the face!
- Shut up! Mr Gazzo wants the 200 now.

96
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:57,875
I'm broke!

97
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:01,037
Mr Gazzo says I should get the 200
or break your thumb.

98
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:04,596
- Please! Please! Don't break my...
- What's your name again?

99
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:07,439
- Bob!
- Listen, Bob...

100
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:11,034
You wanna dance,
you gotta pay the band.

101
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:13,310
You wanna borrow,
you gotta pay the man.

102
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:18,070
Hey, I ain't emotionally involved, Bob,
you understand? Gimme some money.

103
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:20,475
Gimme some money. Come on.

104
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:27,030
- There's 130 here.
- That's it. I'm broke.

105
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:28,957
Hey, Bob. Hey, hey.

106
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:31,036
You're still $70 light.

107
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:36,075
You don't have to break nothin'. Here,
take my coat. It's worth 50, 60 dollars.

108
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,919
Here, take the coat. Take the coat!

109
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:41,918
- Be smart.
- You shoulda planned ahead, you know?

110
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:44,600
- You shoulda planned ahead.
- I'll tape up the hand!

111
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,871
- You shoulda planned ahead.
- Gazzo won't have to know!

112
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:51,675
He won't be wise to nothin'.
Gazzo won't be wise to nothin'!

113
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,676
He won't...

114
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:25,228
He only had 130, but I think he's
good for the rest next week, Mr Gazzo.

115
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:27,715
Sure, Rocky. Bob's good for it.

116
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:32,999
That's it for today.
Tomorrow collect from Del Rio.

117
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:37,477
- He's late three weeks and I don't like it.
- Tomorrow, three weeks, Del Rio.

118
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,716
I got it. How do you spell Del Rio?

119
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:41,876
- How'd you do last night?
- Real good.

120
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:45,913
- Hey, did you get the licence number?
- Of what?

121
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:49,999
- The truck that run over your face.
- Relax, buddy. Pull it over here.

122
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:53,032
I wanna let Rocky out,
then I'm gonna talk to him.

123
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:17,196
How come you didn't break his thumb?

124
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:19,515
- How do you know I didn't?
- I hear things.

125
00:14:19,640 --> 00:14:21,949
- Did I give you a job this mornin'?
- Yeah.

126
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:24,116
So why didn't you break his thumb?

127
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:27,915
When you don't do what I tell you to do,
you make me look bad, Rock.

128
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:32,670
I figured... Look, if I break the guy's
thumb, he gets laid off, right? He can't...

129
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:37,351
Well, let me do the figurin', OK, Rock?
From here on, just let me do the figurin'.

130
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:41,359
These guys think we're runnin'
a charity and they're gonna get off light.

131
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:43,835
From here on in,
do what I tell you to do...

132
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:48,317
...because it's bad for my reputation,
you understand? You got it, Rock?

133
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:51,196
I got it.

134
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:55,310
Hey, how do you spell Del Rio?

135
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:57,749
- Look in a dictionary, Rock!
- Come on!

136
00:14:57,880 --> 00:15:01,509
Hey, I won't let that happen no more -
about the thumb.

137
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:05,035
You know?

138
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:07,390
So long, meatbag.

139
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:12,000
I shoulda broke <i>your</i> thumbs!

140
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:43,669
- I heard you did real good last night.
- Absolutely. You shoulda seen me.

141
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:46,268
- You oughta take a rest.
- No, my back is hurtin'.

142
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:48,994
- Your back?
- My back is hurtin'. You deaf?

143
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,917
No, I'm short.

144
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:51,712
Hey, yo, Mike. Where's my lock?
Whose stuff is this in my locker?

145
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:54,877
It's Dipper's stuff.
It ain't your locker no more.

146
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:01,518
What you talkin' about? It's been my
locker for six years. Where's my gear?

147
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:04,393
Mickey told me to bag it and hang it.

148
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:10,595
You put my stuff on skid row?

149
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:14,395
I been in that locker for six years
and you put my stuff on skid row?

150
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,954
Mickey tells me what to do, I gotta do it.

151
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:20,993
- Where is he?
- He's outside, working with Dipper.

152
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:23,680
- He's in a bad mood.
- So am I.

153
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:37,637
Put your hands up there. That's right.
Keep your hands up. That's right.

154
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:40,274
- Hey, Mick.
- Shut up!

155
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,356
<i>(trainer)</i> Attaboy!

156
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:46,196
Time! Time!

157
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:51,151
- What the hell...? What do you want?
- How you feelin' today?

158
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:54,989
- What are you, a doctor or somethin'?
- You got problems today?

159
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:58,908
- Never mind my problem. What's yours?
- I've been talkin' to Michael.

160
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:02,749
- How come I been put outta my locker?
- Because Dipper needed it.

161
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:05,758
Dipper's a contender, a climber.
Know what you are?

162
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:07,632
- What?
- A tomato.

163
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:11,673
Yeah, let's face it. I run a business here,
not a goddamn soup kitchen.

164
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,597
- Did you fight last night?
- Yeah.

165
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:16,632
- Did you win?
- Yeah, I won KO in the second.

166
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:19,320
- Yeah? Who'd you fight?
- Spider Rico.

167
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:22,034
<i>(laughs)</i> He's a bum!

168
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:25,470
- You think everybody I fight is a bum.
- Well, ain't they?

169
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:30,116
You got heart, but you fight like a
goddamn ape. Nothin' special about you.

170
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:35,075
You never got your nose busted. Leave it
that way, and what's left of your mind.

171
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,919
Mick, I think I'll go take a steam.
You know why?

172
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:40,679
I did real good last night.
You shoulda seen me.

173
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:43,189
- Big deal.
- You shoulda seen me too.

174
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:46,471
Hey, kid, you ever think about retiring?

175
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:49,034
- No.
- You think about it.

176
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:51,390
- All right. Time!
- <i>(Dipper)</i> Hey, hey!

177
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:54,080
- What?
- I dig your locker, man.

178
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:34,108
Cold night.

179
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:37,198
Good night to catch pneumonia,
you know?

180
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:42,999
You need some help with that cage?

181
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:46,271
There's a good game
down at the Spectrum tonight.

182
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:50,960
You wanna go to a basketball game?

183
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:56,229
- <i>(dog barks)</i>
- Hi, Butkus. Hi, kid.

184
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:00,629
Tough day today.
They took my locker away.

185
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:03,558
I had that locker for six years,
but it don't bother me.

186
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:06,399
Lockers are bad.
People get the combination.

187
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:10,149
I must've had 20 bucks taken
outta there in the past six years.

188
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,430
It don't sound like much, but it adds up.

189
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:15,154
You know? It doesn't matter. Who cares?

190
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:20,671
Cold night... Hey, birds!
Hey, look who's here!

191
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:23,360
Look who's here. The giant worm.

192
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:28,558
Look at these birds. Don't these birds
look like candy? Like flyin' candy.

193
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:30,511
Want to fly me home?

194
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:33,313
Do you need somebody
to walk you home, you know?

195
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,873
No.

196
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,709
It's a cold night. If I was you and
you got the money, I would take a cab.

197
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:41,354
Too many creeps around here, you know?

198
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:45,837
Every other block there's a creep.
You can always tell a creep.

199
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:51,829
All right, listen. I'm gonna go now.
I'll see ya's later, all right?

200
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:55,555
Now you guys get up.
I know you had a hard day in the cage.

201
00:20:55,680 --> 00:21:00,435
So... I wanna go home, make up a joke.
I'll tell you a new joke tomorrow, OK?

202
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:03,313
- Good night, Adrian.
- Good night, Rocky.

203
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:23,116
Yo!

204
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:27,278
There you go. I got a friend for you here.

205
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:30,472
- Hello, Rock.
- How you doin'? You seen Paulie?

206
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,477
He's in the steam room.

207
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:35,353
- Hey, Rocky, what's with the eye?
- Been fightin'.

208
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:39,837
- Hope ya's won it, at least.
- I did real good. You shoulda seen me.

209
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:44,994
- Hey, Rock, who'd you fight?
- Spider Rico.

210
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:48,157
- Hey, is he still around?
- Yeah, he's doin' real good.

211
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:53,832
He's doin' better than you are, that's
for sure! Hey, Paulie, you lock the door?

212
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:56,633
I'd like to kill the moron
who broke the mirror.

213
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:58,830
Hey, yo, Paulie!

214
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:03,078
Every day, every night I pass by.
Your sister's givin' me the shoulder.

215
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:06,670
- Forget her. You could do better than her.
- I don't forget nothin'.

216
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:11,430
Every night, I pass by the place, I tell
a joke. Every mornin', I tell a joke. Nothin'.

217
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:13,551
She just looks at me, you know?

218
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:16,592
- Looks, huh?
- Yeah, like I'm a plate of leftovers.

219
00:22:16,720 --> 00:22:21,077
I need a Cadillac to connect with your
sister? Somethin' wrong with my face?

220
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:24,670
She's a freakin' loser.
Sometimes she gets me so crazy...

221
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:27,997
...I could split her head with a razor.
- Don't get mental, man.

222
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:30,554
- You caught me in a bad mood.
- You always are.

223
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:33,877
- Adrian ain't sharp. Adrian is a loser.
- Hey!

224
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:38,391
She's pushin' 30 years old and if she
don't watch out she'll end up dyin' alone.

