go out together and get somethin' to eat?

438
00:36:51,200 --> 00:36:53,873
I don't know,
maybe laugh a little bit. Who knows?

439
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:56,355
Would you like to, uh...

440
00:36:57,320 --> 00:37:02,269
I don't know. Would you like to maybe,
you know, you and me go out together?

441
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,788
We're gonna have a good time.

442
00:37:09,920 --> 00:37:13,310
We'll have a real good time, you know?

443
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:18,795
Thanks for the bird.

444
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:24,478
I'm gonna turn the TV off.
I got a headache.

445
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:38,475
- What's your sister like to do?
- Ice-skate.

446
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:43,549
Adrian, come on, you're lettin' the heat
out. Who pays the bills around here?

447
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:51,589
Listen, uh, I don't want
no turkey anyway, you know?

448
00:37:52,640 --> 00:37:56,189
- But it was Thanksgiving.
- It was what?

449
00:37:56,320 --> 00:38:00,472
- It was Thanksgiving.
- Yeah, to you, but to me it's Thursday.

450
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:26,548
- Yo, looks kinda quiet.
- I think it's closed.

451
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:29,717
No, I think we're just early
or somethin' like that.

452
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,034
- Yo!
- Yo!

453
00:38:31,160 --> 00:38:33,071
- We're closed!
- What?

454
00:38:33,200 --> 00:38:35,919
- I said we're closed!
- Yeah. Hey, listen...

455
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:39,191
...l'm gonna smooth this guy out.
Wait here for a few minutes.

456
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:41,515
- We could go someplace else.
- No, it's OK.

457
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:44,950
Are you closed to the general public
or closed to everybody?

458
00:38:45,080 --> 00:38:49,392
It's after six o'clock. It's Thanksgiving.
That's why there's nobody here.

459
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:53,638
Besides, you ain't supposed to be in here,
so do me a favour and leave, huh?

460
00:38:53,760 --> 00:38:57,548
- Could you do me a favour?
- Hey, come on, we're not operatin'.

461
00:38:57,680 --> 00:39:00,319
Look... this girl here ain't feelin' well.

462
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:04,877
The doctor says she should exercise
and ice-skating's the best thing.

463
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:09,198
- Yeah? So what do you want from me?
- Do me a favour. She ain't feelin' good.

464
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:12,676
So if you could let her on the ice,
I'd appreciate it.

465
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:16,588
- Ten minutes, ten bucks.
- Ten bucks? How about eight bucks?

466
00:39:16,720 --> 00:39:18,950
Come on! It's Thanksgiving.

467
00:39:19,080 --> 00:39:24,029
- All right. Nine bucks, you got a deal.
- You have the ice to yourself. Ten bucks.

468
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:27,238
Gimme the blades.

469
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:31,112
- Aren't you skating?
- No, I ain't skated since I was 15.

470
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:33,549
That's when I started fightin'.

471
00:39:33,680 --> 00:39:37,150
- Skating's bad for the ankles, you know?
- Yeah.

472
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:39,840
You're a pretty good skater, ain't ya?

473
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:45,993
Like I was sayin' on the way over, fightin'
used to be tops with me, but no more.

474
00:39:46,120 --> 00:39:48,634
All I wanted to do was
prove I was no bum...

475
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:51,069
...that I had the stuff to make a good pro.

476
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:54,670
- You never got the chance?
- I ain't cryin', cos I still fight.

477
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:58,156
I kinda do it like a hobby.
The trouble is, I'm a southpaw.

478
00:39:58,280 --> 00:40:01,158
- What's a southpaw?
- It means you're left-handed.

479
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:03,510
A southpaw throws your timin' off, see?

480
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:07,428
Other guys, it makes 'em look awkward.
Nobody wants to look awkward.

481
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:10,996
- You know where southpaw came from?
- <i>(attendant)</i> Nine minutes!

482
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:14,908
A long time ago, a couple of hundred
years ago, this guy was fightin'.

483
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:18,350
I think it was around Philadelphia.
He was left-handed.

484
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:20,789
His arm was facin' towards New Jersey.

485
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:24,037
And that's south,
so they called him Southpaw.

486
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:26,754
You see? Southpaw, South Jersey...

487
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:29,997
...South Camden, Southpaw...
You know what I mean?

488
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:33,551
Things worked out for the best.

489
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:36,194
You never got a chance,
being left-handed?

490
00:40:36,320 --> 00:40:39,869
Well, that's absolutely true,
you know? Watch out, watch out.

491
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:42,833
Agh! Agh! Agh!

492
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:46,157
I just dislocated my finger.
Agh! Look at that.

493
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:48,589
No, hey, wait! It ain't your fault. Look.

494
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:51,632
See? Look.
It's an old wound. You see that?

495
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:55,435
Look. See? Nothin'.
It bends like that. I originally done it...

496
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:57,516
Push the button... Bong! It works.

497
00:40:57,640 --> 00:41:00,996
- It ain't your fault. I'll show you...
- Seven minutes!

498
00:41:01,120 --> 00:41:04,032
I originally done it...
I keep pictures of all my fights.

499
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:06,594
I done it in the Baby Crenshaw fight. See?

500
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:09,713
He's the size of an airplane.
I broke both my hands.

501
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:15,676
I lost that fight, but that's a nice picture,
don't you think? See how it works there?

502
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:17,791
Come on. Are you havin' a good time?

503
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:21,833
I'll tell ya, you can see I ain't too graceful.
I don't move well.

504
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:24,872
But I can really swat, you know?
I can really hit hard.

505
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:29,949
But I'm a southpaw and nobody wants to
fight a southpaw, you know what I mean?

506
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:35,995
Whooo!
You know how I got started in fightin'?

507
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:38,076
- Huh?
- No.

508
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:40,191
Am I talkin' too loud?

509
00:41:40,320 --> 00:41:41,673
- No.
- Three minutes!

510
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:46,157
My father, he's...
My old man, he was never too smart.

511
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:50,717
He says to me "You weren't born
much of a brain, so start usin' your body."

512
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:53,195
So I've become a fighter.

513
00:41:53,320 --> 00:41:56,676
You know what I mean?
Why are you laughin'?

514
00:41:58,040 --> 00:42:00,759
My mother, she said the opposite thing.

515
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:03,519
What did she say?
What did she say, the opposite?

516
00:42:03,640 --> 00:42:07,633
"You weren't born much of a body,
so you'd better develop your brain."

517
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:10,797
- Did she say that?
- Yo! Time!

518
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:14,398
- Can I ask you a question?
- Absolutely.

519
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:18,598
- Why do you wanna fight?
- Cos I can't sing or dance.

520
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:20,312
Hey, yo!

521
00:42:20,440 --> 00:42:23,079
Don't fall! Don't fall!

522
00:42:23,200 --> 00:42:26,875
Hey, that was terrific. I'm good at this.
You like the way I skate?

523
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,878
The last fight I had was
with a guy named Spider Rico.

524
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:32,594
He bust my head up.
Do you see that scar?

525
00:42:32,720 --> 00:42:35,518
I'll tell ya,
things get pretty rough in the ring.

526
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:48,155
You know, some people are
very shy by nature, you know?

527
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:50,236
I suppose.

528
00:42:52,640 --> 00:42:55,313
I say you're very shy by nature,
you know?

529
00:42:55,440 --> 00:42:57,396
Yeah... I suppose.

530
00:42:58,480 --> 00:43:00,198
Hey! Hey!

531
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:03,551
The bum from the dock.
Get a job, ya bum!

532
00:43:04,600 --> 00:43:09,151
You know, some people think bein' shy
is a disease, but it don't bother me none.

533
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:11,430
It don't bother me, either.

534
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:16,154
Why did I bother bringin' it up?
Cos I'm dumb, that's why.

535
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:22,595
I think we make a real sharp couple
of coconuts. I'm dumb, you're shy.

536
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:28,315
I don't understand why anybody
would wanna be a fighter.

537
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:30,476
Hey, you gotta be a moron.

538
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:33,956
You gotta be a moron to wanna be
a fighter, you know what I mean?

539
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:37,390
It's a racket where you're almost
guaranteed to end up a bum.

540
00:43:37,520 --> 00:43:40,910
- I don't think you're a bum.
- I'm at least half a bum, you know?

541
00:43:41,040 --> 00:43:43,759
I'll tell ya somethin'.

542
00:43:43,880 --> 00:43:47,395
The worst thing about fightin'
is the mornin' after, you know?

543
00:43:47,520 --> 00:43:52,150
I'll tell ya. The mornin' after a fight, you're
nothin' but a large wound, you know?

544
00:43:52,280 --> 00:43:54,236
Sometimes I got pains all over me.

545
00:43:54,360 --> 00:43:57,796
I wanna call a taxi to take me
from the bed into the bathroom.

546
00:43:57,920 --> 00:44:02,471
Your hair hurts, your eyes hurt, your face
is all busted up, your hands is swollen.

547
00:44:02,600 --> 00:44:06,752
Look at this face. 64 fights.
Look at that nose. See that nose?

548
00:44:06,880 --> 00:44:09,110
That nose ain't been broken in 64 fights.

549
00:44:09,240 --> 00:44:13,597
I've had guys bustin' on it,
chewin' on it, twistin' it, punchin' it.

550
00:44:13,720 --> 00:44:17,759
I mean, whack, boom. These guys
are hittin' my nose all the time.

551
00:44:17,880 --> 00:44:21,350
Never broke. I'm proud of that.
Ain't that rare? That's rare.

552
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:24,597
- Why do you do it if it hurts?
- Why you think?

553
00:44:25,760 --> 00:44:30,675
- Cos you can't sing or dance?
- Yeah, somethin' like that.

554
00:44:30,800 --> 00:44:32,870
Hey, you wanna come inside?

555
00:44:35,320 --> 00:44:38,232
- No, I gotta go.
- Hey, come on. I got some animals.

556
00:44:38,360 --> 00:44:42,114
I got these very rare animals inside.
Come on. Come on in.

557
00:44:42,240 --> 00:44:47,030
- No, no. I gotta go.
- I gotta go too. I gotta go to the bathroom.

558
00:44:47,160 --> 00:44:49,674
- Go on.
- No, I gotta go.

559
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:52,712
Hey, look at this face.
Is that a face you could trust?

560
00:44:52,840 --> 00:44:57,550
Huh? Is it? They oughta stick this face
on a stamp. What do you think?

561
00:44:57,680 --> 00:45:00,035
Huh? Come on. Come on in.

562
00:45:05,440 --> 00:45:07,670
Yo.

563
00:45:26,680 --> 00:45:28,636
Flick.

564
00:45:33,240 --> 00:45:36,232
- Yo, Adrian, you hungry?
- No.

565
00:45:36,360 --> 00:45:40,956
I got some things in there. I got soda,
some doughnuts or somethin'.

566
00:45:41,080 --> 00:45:43,275
A couple of cupcakes, huh?

567
00:45:43,400 --> 00:45:46,517
No? I think I got some chocolate in there.

568
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:48,596
No?

569
00:45:55,480 --> 00:45:57,835
Hot in here, you know?

570
00:45:59,240 --> 00:46:01,595
I could go for some music.

571
00:46:06,640 --> 00:46:08,392
Yo, Adrian.

572
00:46:08,520 --> 00:46:11,080
These are the exotic animals
I told you about.

573
00:46:11,200 --> 00:46:14,431
- These are my friends Cuff and Link.
- I sold 'em to ya.

574
00:46:14,560 --> 00:46:18,314
Sure, I know you sold 'em to me.
You were workin' at that pet shop.

575
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:21,796
First day you was there,
I bought both these animals.

576
00:46:21,920 --> 00:46:26,675
Sure, I remember that. I bought this bowl
and I bought the animals themselves...

577
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:29,758
...the food,
the marbles that go on the bottom there.

578
00:46:29,880 --> 00:46:35,637
Remember that mountain? I had to get rid
of it, cos they kept fallin' over and flippin'.

579
00:46:38,600 --> 00:46:41,353
Yo, why don't you come on
over here and sit down?

580
00:46:41,480 --> 00:46:43,311
Hm?

581
00:46:43,440 --> 00:46:45,590
It's a nice couch. I don't know...

582
00:46:47,560 --> 00:46:51,348
There's big bugs in there, you know?
It's safer over here.

583
00:46:53,160 --> 00:46:55,116
You wanna sit down?

584
00:47:00,440 --> 00:47:02,635
Are these your parents?

585
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:04,990
Yeah, that's both of 'em there.

586
00:47:05,120 --> 00:47:07,634
- Is this you?
- Yeah, that's me when I was eight.

587
00:47:07,760 --> 00:47:10,957
That's the Italian Stallion
when he was a baby.

588
00:47:12,880 --> 00:47:17,237
Why don't you come on over and
make yourself comfortable? Relax.

589
00:47:21,120 --> 00:47:23,634
- Do you have a phone?
- No, I ain't got no phone.

590
00:47:23,760 --> 00:47:26,957
I had it pulled,
cos of people callin' all the time.

591
00:47:27,080 --> 00:47:30,550
Who needs the aggravation, right?
The interruptions.

592
00:47:30,680 --> 00:47:34,832
- Who do you wanna call?
- I wanna let my brother know where I am.

593
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:38,149
Why?

594
00:47:38,280 --> 00:47:43,035
- I think he might be worried.
- Well, I'll call him, if that's the problem.

595
00:47:45,440 --> 00:47:50,230
Yo, Paulie! Your sister's with me!
I'll call ya's back later! See ya!

596
00:47:56,560 --> 00:47:58,630
You don't like the room, do ya?

597
00:47:58,760 --> 00:48:01,832
- It's fine.
- Well, it's only temporary, you know?

598
00:48:02,120 --> 00:48:04,076
It's not that.

599
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:13,389
What's the problem? You don't like <i>me?</i>
Or the turtles? What's the problem?

600
00:48:13,680 --> 00:48:16,478
- I don't think I belong here.
- It's OK.

601
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:21,275
I don't belong here.

602
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:25,439
Well, you know, it's OK,
cos you're my guest, you know?

603
00:48:25,560 --> 00:48:28,313
I don't... know you well enough.

604
00:48:28,440 --> 00:48:32,228
I've never been in
a man's apartment alone.

605
00:48:33,440 --> 00:48:36,398
Well, I have.
They're all the same, you know?

606
00:48:41,120 --> 00:48:43,680
I'm not sure I know you well enough.

607
00:48:44,840 --> 00:48:46,876
I don't feel comfortable.

608
00:48:47,000 --> 00:48:50,754
Yo, Adrian, you know,
I ain't so comfortable either.

609
00:48:52,040 --> 00:48:55,271
- I should go.
- Don't go, please. Don't go.

610
00:48:55,400 --> 00:48:57,709
Don't go. Don't go.

611
00:48:57,840 --> 00:48:59,796
Don't go.

612
00:49:02,600 --> 00:49:05,239
- Do me a favour?
- What?

613
00:49:05,360 --> 00:49:07,715
Take off these glasses.

614
00:49:10,840 --> 00:49:13,195
You have nice eyes, you know?

615
00:49:14,720 --> 00:49:17,393
Do me another favour?

616
00:49:17,520 --> 00:49:19,875
Would you take off that hat?

617
00:49:25,840 --> 00:49:28,195
I always knew you was pretty.

618
00:49:29,160 --> 00:49:31,913
- Don't tease me.
- I'm not teasin' ya.

619
00:49:35,080 --> 00:49:37,719
I ain't teasin' ya.

620
00:49:37,840 --> 00:49:40,195
I just... I wanna kiss ya.

621
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:45,917
You don't have to kiss me back
if you don't want...

622
00:49:46,040 --> 00:49:47,996
...but I wanna kiss you.

623
00:50:56,840 --> 00:50:58,796
I heard you had a fight comin' up.

624
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:01,798
Yeah, I'm gonna fight next month,
January 27th.

625
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:06,914
That's good, man. You come on down
the gym. We'll see that you get in shape.

626
00:51:07,040 --> 00:51:08,951
Hey, Rock, how you doin'?

627
00:51:09,080 --> 00:51:12,152
- Mick was lookin' for you up there, man.
- For me? You sure?

628
00:51:12,280 --> 00:51:16,432
Yeah, yeah, yeah. He was lookin' for you.
Get on up there and see him.

629
00:51:33,520 --> 00:51:37,718
- You got somethin' for me?
- A guy from Miles Jergens was here.

630
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:41,753
- They need sparrin' partners for Creed.
- When was he here?

631
00:51:41,880 --> 00:51:45,953
- About an hour ago.
- Probably lookin' for sparrin' partners.

632
00:51:46,360 --> 00:51:49,033
I said that before, you dumb dago!

633
00:51:50,080 --> 00:51:54,312
I've been comin' here for six years
and you always stick it to me. How come?

634
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:57,318
- You don't wanna know!
- Yeah, I wanna know how come!

635
00:51:57,440 --> 00:51:59,476
- You wanna know?
- I wanna know!

636
00:51:59,600 --> 00:52:04,196
OK, I'm gonna tell ya! Cos you had
the talent to become a good fighter!

637
00:52:04,320 --> 00:52:07,039
And instead of that,
you became a leg-breaker...

638
00:52:07,160 --> 00:52:10,197
...to some cheap, second-rate loan shark!

639
00:52:10,320 --> 00:52:13,232
- It's a livin'.
- It's a waste of life!

640
00:52:31,240 --> 00:52:33,390
Yes? May I help you?

641
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:40,310
Oh! You must be Mr Rocky Balboa.

642
00:52:40,440 --> 00:52:43,398
Mr Jergens is expecting you.
Just a moment.

643
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:50,913
Mr Rocky Balboa to see you, sir.

644
00:52:51,040 --> 00:52:52,951
Fine.

645
00:52:53,080 --> 00:52:55,355
- Please go in, Mr Balboa.
- Can I have that?

646
00:52:55,480 --> 00:52:57,835
- Oh, certainly.
- Thanks.

647
00:53:02,160 --> 00:53:04,196
Mr Balboa.

648
00:53:04,320 --> 00:53:07,790
How are you? George Jergens.
Take a chair, please.

649
00:53:07,920 --> 00:53:09,876
Thanks.

650
00:53:10,680 --> 00:53:13,240
- Mr Balboa...
- You can call me Rocky.

651
00:53:13,360 --> 00:53:17,751
Rocky. Tell me, Rocky. You got any
representation? You have a manager?

652
00:53:17,880 --> 00:53:19,836
Uh, no, just me.

653
00:53:20,960 --> 00:53:24,509
Rocky, I've got a proposition
I'd like to make to you.

654
00:53:24,640 --> 00:53:27,871
- About sparrin'?
- I beg your pardon?

655
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:32,357
I know you're lookin' for sparrin' partners
and I wanna say I'm very available.

656
00:53:32,480 --> 00:53:35,677
- I'm sure you are.
- Absolutely. It would be an honour.

657
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:38,758
And you know what?
I wouldn't take no cheap shots.

658
00:53:38,880 --> 00:53:43,670
- I'd really be a good sparrin' partner.
- You don't understand me, Rocky.

659
00:53:43,800 --> 00:53:48,669
My proposition's this. Would you be
interested in fighting Apollo Creed...

660
00:53:48,800 --> 00:53:51,553
...for the world
heavyweight championship?

661
00:53:55,880 --> 00:53:58,235
- No.
- Listen, Rocky...

662
00:53:59,480 --> 00:54:01,596
...Apollo's seen you fight.

663
00:54:02,080 --> 00:54:05,038
He likes you. He wants to fight you.

664
00:54:05,160 --> 00:54:08,914
Well, it's just that, you see, uh,
I fight in clubs, you know?

665
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:13,431
I'm really a ham and egger. This guy is
the best. It wouldn't be such a good fight.

666
00:54:13,560 --> 00:54:17,348
But thank you very much,
you know? I appreciate it.

667
00:54:17,720 --> 00:54:21,952
Rocky, do you believe that America
is the land of opportunity?

668
00:54:23,240 --> 00:54:24,912
Yeah.

669
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:27,031
Apollo Creed does.

670
00:54:27,160 --> 00:54:31,790
And he's gonna prove it to the world
by giving an unknown a shot at the title.

671
00:54:31,920 --> 00:54:34,639
And that unknown is you.

672
00:54:34,760 --> 00:54:36,910
He picked you, Rocky.

673
00:54:37,720 --> 00:54:40,837
Rocky, it's the chance of a lifetime.

674
00:54:40,960 --> 00:54:43,110
You can't pass it by.

675
00:54:44,000 --> 00:54:46,150
What do ya say?

676
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:53,868
<i>All right. That's enough pictures.</i>
<i>We wanna ask Apollo a few questions.</i>

677
00:54:53,960 --> 00:54:56,394
<i>How do you like</i>
<i>the city of brotherly love?</i>

678
00:54:56,520 --> 00:54:59,830
<i>Well, just bein' in Philadelphia</i>
<i>makes me feel patriotic.</i>

679
00:54:59,960 --> 00:55:03,509
<i>Beautiful people in a beautiful city</i>
<i>wishin' me the best.</i>

680
00:55:03,640 --> 00:55:06,996
<i>I love my Philadelphia brothers.</i>
<i>I'm proud to be an American.</i>

681
00:55:07,120 --> 00:55:11,671
<i>Apollo, why did you agree to fight a man</i>
<i>who has virtually no chance of winning?</i>

682
00:55:11,800 --> 00:55:13,916
<i>Look, if history proves one thing...</i>

683
00:55:14,040 --> 00:55:17,555
<i>American history proves that</i>
<i>everybody's got a chance to win.</i>

684
00:55:17,680 --> 00:55:21,150
<i>Didn't you guys ever hear of</i>
<i>Valley Forge or Bunker Hill?</i>

685
00:55:21,280 --> 00:55:24,352
<i>It is a coincidence that</i>
<i>you're fighting a white man...</i>

686
00:55:24,480 --> 00:55:26,675
<i>... on the most celebrated day</i>
<i>in US history?</i>

687
00:55:26,800 --> 00:55:32,193
<i>I don't know. Is it a coincidence that he's</i>
<i>fightin' a black man on the same day?</i>

688
00:55:32,320 --> 00:55:34,276
<i>Right on! Tell the truth, brother!</i>

689
00:55:34,400 --> 00:55:36,789
<i>How do you feel about your challenger?</i>

690
00:55:36,920 --> 00:55:39,878
<i>How do I feel about him?</i>
<i>Come here, Rock.</i>

691
00:55:40,000 --> 00:55:43,834
<i>- My main man. Rocky, ain't you Italian?</i>
<i>- Yeah, I'm Italian.</i>

692
00:55:43,960 --> 00:55:48,511
<i>- Well now, what does that mean?</i>
<i>- If he can't fight, I bet he can cook!</i>

693
00:55:50,080 --> 00:55:53,914
- Do me a favour. His lungs, punch out.
- Paulie!

694
00:55:54,040 --> 00:55:57,316
<i>Rocky,</i>
<i>how do you expect to fight Apollo Creed?</i>

695
00:55:57,440 --> 00:56:01,399
<i>Well, jeez, Creed's the best.</i>
<i>I guess I'll have to do the best I can.</i>

696
00:56:01,520 --> 00:56:04,193
<i>Tell me, Rocky. Just between us...</i>

697
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:07,118
<i>... where did you get</i>
<i>the name "ltalian Stallion"?</i>

698
00:56:07,240 --> 00:56:11,472
<i>Oh, I invented that about eight years ago</i>
<i>when I was eatin' dinner.</i>

699
00:56:11,600 --> 00:56:17,470
<i>Rocky, now your payday will be $150,000.</i>
<i>Any comment?</i>

700
00:56:19,160 --> 00:56:21,390
<i>- You got no comment, Rocky, right?</i>
<i>- No.</i>

701
00:56:21,520 --> 00:56:23,238
<i>No comment, right.</i>

702
00:56:23,360 --> 00:56:26,830
<i>Wait a minute.</i>
<i>I just wanna say hi to my girlfriend, OK?</i>

703
00:56:26,960 --> 00:56:31,078
<i>Yo, Adrian! It's me, Rocky.</i>
<i>Look at this. Can you believe all this?</i>

704
00:56:31,200 --> 00:56:34,033
Rocky, you didn't...!

705
00:56:34,160 --> 00:56:36,958
<i>- Thank you, Rocky.</i>
<i>- Quit pushin', man!</i>

706
00:56:37,080 --> 00:56:38,149
<i>Thank you, Rocky.</i>

707
00:56:38,280 --> 00:56:42,114
Don't it matter he's makin' you out a fool?
I'd break his lips.

708
00:56:42,240 --> 00:56:45,277
- He's takin' cheap shots.
- It don't bother me none.

709
00:56:45,400 --> 00:56:50,235
Yo, Rock. I guess you'd be lookin'
for people to help you out.

710
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:52,920
- Help what?
- You know...

711
00:56:53,040 --> 00:56:56,715
- Keep you livin' a clean life.
- I do OK, you know?

712
00:56:56,840 --> 00:57:00,992
You need someone to help with
the exercise, stand by with a towel...

713
00:57:01,120 --> 00:57:02,758
...run errands.

714
00:57:02,880 --> 00:57:07,715
Who cared about me yesterday? Nobody.
I think I'm gonna train myself, you know?

715
00:57:07,840 --> 00:57:12,550
Without such good people around to help,
you don't have such a good chance.

716
00:57:12,680 --> 00:57:15,478
Einstein flunked outta school. Twice.

717
00:57:15,600 --> 00:57:17,795
- That so?
- Yeah.

718
00:57:17,920 --> 00:57:23,199
Beethoven was deaf, Helen Keller was
blind. I think Rocky's got a good chance.

719
00:57:28,960 --> 00:57:32,475
- Want me to get you a beer, Paulie?
- You lookin' to do a good deed?

720
00:57:32,600 --> 00:57:35,319
Keep outta my freakin' life!

721
00:57:35,680 --> 00:57:37,636
- What did I do?
- Nothin'.

722
00:57:37,760 --> 00:57:40,479
- Did I say something?
- You didn't say nothin'.

723
00:57:40,600 --> 00:57:44,673
That's right, you didn't say nothin'!
Nothin' at all!

724
00:57:46,240 --> 00:57:48,196
I gotta go.

725
00:57:48,760 --> 00:57:51,115
Where's the freakin' pretzels?

726
00:57:54,000 --> 00:57:57,549
Goddamn the pretzels!
Hey, we don't have any beer!

727
00:57:58,680 --> 00:58:02,036
I thought you were supposed
to pick up some beer!

728
00:58:09,280 --> 00:58:12,556
How'd you like hearin'
your name on TV tonight?

729
00:58:13,600 --> 00:58:16,194
I was shocked. Why'd you do that?

730
00:58:16,320 --> 00:58:20,029
- Come on, you're puttin' me on, right?
- Absolutely.

731
00:58:20,160 --> 00:58:23,789
- What time should I expect you?
- Oh, about seven.

732
00:58:23,920 --> 00:58:25,876
Hey.

733
00:58:38,800 --> 00:58:40,756
Hey.

734
00:58:41,720 --> 00:58:45,190
You know I said that stuff on TV
didn't bother me none?

735
00:58:45,320 --> 00:58:47,276
Yeah?

736
00:58:48,920 --> 00:58:50,876
It did.

737
00:59:00,360 --> 00:59:03,636
Listen, the reason I've
brought you here is because...

738
00:59:03,760 --> 00:59:06,069
Have you got money
for trainin' expenses?

739
00:59:06,200 --> 00:59:09,988
- I got a few dollars, you know?
- Well, here. Put this in your glove.

740
00:59:10,120 --> 00:59:13,476
- What's this?
- 500 bucks. Don't worry about it.

741
00:59:14,400 --> 00:59:18,473
You ain't never had any luck, but this time
Lady Luck may be in your corner.

742
00:59:18,600 --> 00:59:21,478
- What do ya think?
- Maybe. Maybe...

743
00:59:21,600 --> 00:59:26,674
- Hey, thanks for the money, Tony.
- It's OK. Don't worry about it. See ya.

744
00:59:26,800 --> 00:59:28,199
- Wait a minute.
- What?

745
00:59:28,320 --> 00:59:31,073
- You're in trainin'. Huh? Come on.
- Hey.

746
00:59:38,480 --> 00:59:40,596
- Yo, Tony?
- What?

747
00:59:40,720 --> 00:59:42,711
You gonna show up at the fight?

748
00:59:42,840 --> 00:59:44,956
- Ringside.
- Hey, hey!

749
00:59:46,560 --> 00:59:48,516
I'll see ya.

750
01:00:21,520 --> 01:00:23,476
<i>(Rocky)</i> Yeah!

751
01:00:28,160 --> 01:00:31,436
Hello, kid. I seen your light.
Can I come in?

752
01:00:31,560 --> 01:00:33,630
- Yeah, sure.
- Yeah. Good!

753
01:00:33,760 --> 01:00:36,399
Hey, this is a nice place here.

754
01:00:36,520 --> 01:00:39,557
Anyway, what I come to tell you
is that, uh...

755
01:00:40,720 --> 01:00:43,837
...that what happened to you is freak luck.

756
01:00:43,960 --> 01:00:46,997
- Yeah, freak luck.
- Ain't it true? Look at the other guys.

757
01:00:47,120 --> 01:00:50,795
They're good fighters.
They're colourful, they got good records.

758
01:00:50,920 --> 01:00:53,150
They fight their guts out for peanuts.

759
01:00:53,280 --> 01:00:57,193
But you... you got a shot at the title.

760
01:00:57,320 --> 01:01:00,710
- Freak luck is a strange thing.
- Yeah, sure it is. Can I sit down?

761
01:01:00,840 --> 01:01:03,149
Yeah, sure.

762
01:01:03,280 --> 01:01:06,636
- What the hell are those?
- Oh, they're domestic turtles.

763
01:01:06,760 --> 01:01:10,230
The one on top is Cuff and
the other is Link. The rest are marbles.

764
01:01:10,360 --> 01:01:13,670
Yeah? They make good soup, do they?

765
01:01:13,800 --> 01:01:17,236
Anyway, look, I'm here to warn ya...

766
01:01:17,360 --> 01:01:21,638
...that you gotta be very careful
about this shot that you got at the title.

767
01:01:21,760 --> 01:01:26,595
Because, I don't know, like the Bible says,
you ain't gonna get a second chance.

768
01:01:27,440 --> 01:01:30,671
- Yeah, all right.
- You thought of that, huh?

769
01:01:30,800 --> 01:01:33,837
Well, what you need is a manager.

770
01:01:34,760 --> 01:01:36,796
A manager. Listen to me.

771
01:01:36,920 --> 01:01:40,356
I know, because I've been
in this racket for 50 years.

772
01:01:40,480 --> 01:01:43,597
- 50 years, huh?
- 50 years. God, I've seen it all.

773
01:01:43,720 --> 01:01:46,359
All of it. You know what I done?

774
01:01:46,480 --> 01:01:48,914
- What?
- I have done it all.

775
01:01:49,040 --> 01:01:52,589
You shoulda seen me when
I knocked Giny Russel outta the ring.

776
01:01:52,720 --> 01:01:56,599
Outta the goddamn ring, I tell ya.
September 14, 1923.

777
01:01:56,720 --> 01:02:00,599
And it was the same night that
Firpo knocks Dempsey outta the ring.

778
01:02:00,720 --> 01:02:03,632
- The same night. Who gets the publicity?
- Dempsey.

779
01:02:03,760 --> 01:02:05,955
- That's right, but why?
- Cos he was champ.

780
01:02:06,080 --> 01:02:09,072
No! Because he had a manager.

781
01:02:09,200 --> 01:02:11,714
I had nothin', man.

782
01:02:11,840 --> 01:02:15,276
I wanna show you somethin'.
Look at my face for a minute. Look.

783
01:02:15,400 --> 01:02:20,110
I got 21 stitches over this left eye.
I got 34 stitches over this eye.

784
01:02:20,240 --> 01:02:23,596
You know what?
I had my nose busted 17 times.

785
01:02:23,720 --> 01:02:27,713
The last time was with
that fight with Sailor Mike.

786
01:02:27,840 --> 01:02:30,718
I got the clippin' here. A good fight.

787
01:02:30,840 --> 01:02:32,671
Read that.

788
01:02:32,800 --> 01:02:34,756
Well, it doesn't matter.

789
01:02:34,880 --> 01:02:37,952
Anyway, he put this vegetation on my ear.

790
01:02:39,160 --> 01:02:42,232
Ah, Rocky Marciano!

791
01:02:43,360 --> 01:02:47,273
You know, you kinda remind me
of the Rock, do you know that?

792
01:02:47,400 --> 01:02:50,870
- You really think so?
- That's right. You move like him.

793
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:52,956
And you got heart, like he did.

794
01:02:53,080 --> 01:02:56,197
Yeah, I got heart,
but I ain't got no locker, do I, Mick?

795
01:02:59,760 --> 01:03:02,354
Uh... anyway, you know...

796
01:03:02,480 --> 01:03:05,358
...when I begun in this business, kid...

797
01:03:06,480 --> 01:03:10,996
Look, I wanna make a suggestion.
Don't drink that piss before a fight.

798
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:14,715
It's no good for ya.
You don't mind my sayin'...?

799
01:03:14,840 --> 01:03:19,277
Anyway, when I started this racket,
pugs like us, we was treated like dogs.

800
01:03:19,400 --> 01:03:24,872
For $10, you gotta tear somebody's throat
out. But I never had no management.

801
01:03:25,400 --> 01:03:30,076
One time, this son of a bitch
that I fought, he put a nail right there.

802
01:03:30,200 --> 01:03:32,270
- In his thumb?
- Yeah, in the glove.

803
01:03:32,400 --> 01:03:34,755
And he punched
so many holes in my face...

804
01:03:34,880 --> 01:03:39,795
...I had this spit shootin' outta my cheeks.
Can you imagine that?

805
01:03:39,920 --> 01:03:43,276
When I tell you what I looked like
when I was in my prime...

806
01:03:43,400 --> 01:03:46,153
I want ya to look at somethin'.
Will ya look at that?

807
01:03:46,280 --> 01:03:50,273
That's the way I looked
before these guys got at me.

808
01:03:50,400 --> 01:03:53,790
That's nice.
You don't take care of the picture, though.

809
01:03:53,920 --> 01:03:57,833
Well, I never had no management.
That was the trouble.

810
01:03:57,960 --> 01:04:02,351
Now I got all this knowledge.
I got it up here and I wanna give it to you.

811
01:04:02,480 --> 01:04:06,871
I wanna take care of you. I wanna make
sure all this shit that happened to me...

812
01:04:07,000 --> 01:04:10,515
...doesn't happen to you.
You know what I mean?

813
01:04:10,640 --> 01:04:14,269
- The fight's set.
- Listen to me. I wanna be your manager.

814
01:04:14,400 --> 01:04:17,949
- You follow that, do you?
- The fight's set. I don't need no manager.

815
01:04:18,080 --> 01:04:22,471
But you can't buy what I'm gonna give ya.
I've got pain and I've got experience.

816
01:04:22,600 --> 01:04:25,637
I got pain and I got experience too.

817
01:04:25,760 --> 01:04:29,275
- Now listen, kid...
- Hey, yo. Hey, Mick.

818
01:04:29,400 --> 01:04:33,279
I needed your help about ten years ago.
You never helped me none.

819
01:04:33,400 --> 01:04:36,472
- You didn't care.
- Well, if you wanted help...

820
01:04:36,600 --> 01:04:40,479
I say, if you wanted help,
why didn't you just ask me, kid?

821
01:04:40,600 --> 01:04:43,956
Look, I asked,
but you never heard nothin'!

822
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:46,036
Well, I...

823
01:04:46,840 --> 01:04:48,796
I, uh...

824
01:04:49,600 --> 01:04:51,955
I'm 76 years old.

825
01:04:56,000 --> 01:04:57,956
And, uh...

826
01:05:19,400 --> 01:05:21,356
Ah, shit.

827
01:05:31,440 --> 01:05:34,273
Took you long enough to get here.

828
01:05:34,400 --> 01:05:39,076
Ten years to come to my house. What's
the matter? You don't like my house?

829
01:05:39,200 --> 01:05:41,430
My house stink?

830
01:05:41,560 --> 01:05:43,790
That's right. It stinks!

831
01:05:43,920 --> 01:05:46,229
I didn't ask no favours from you!

832
01:05:46,360 --> 01:05:48,351
Don't throw it around!

833
01:05:48,800 --> 01:05:52,713
Talkin' about your prime.
What about <i>my</i> prime, Mick?

834
01:05:53,120 --> 01:05:55,475
At least you had a prime!

835
01:05:55,600 --> 01:06:00,549
I ain't had no prime! I ain't had nothin'!
Legs are goin', everything's goin'!

836
01:06:00,680 --> 01:06:05,674
Guy offers me a fight. Big deal! Wanna
fight the fight? Yeah, I'll fight the big fight.

837
01:06:05,800 --> 01:06:09,190
I'm gonna go and fight that big fight.
I'm gonna get that!

838
01:06:09,320 --> 01:06:11,959
I'm gonna get that!

839
01:06:12,080 --> 01:06:14,833
And you wanna be ringside and see it?
Do ya?

840
01:06:14,960 --> 01:06:18,873
You wanna help me out? Huh? Do you
wanna see me get my face kicked in?

841
01:06:19,000 --> 01:06:23,676
Legs ain't workin', nothing's workin'!
They go "Go on, fight the champ!"

842
01:06:23,800 --> 01:06:25,756
Yeah, I'll fight him.

843
01:06:27,920 --> 01:06:30,559
Get my face kicked in.

844
01:06:30,680 --> 01:06:35,629
You come around here! You wanna move
in with me? Come on in! It's a nice house!

845
01:06:35,760 --> 01:06:38,718
Real nice! Come on in and move! It stinks!

846
01:06:39,640 --> 01:06:41,835
This whole place stinks!

847
01:06:42,280 --> 01:06:45,477
You wanna help me out?
Well, help me out!

848
01:06:45,600 --> 01:06:48,478
Come on! Help me out! I'm standin' here!

849
01:07:35,840 --> 01:07:37,637
<i>(alarm rings)</i>

850
01:07:45,080 --> 01:07:50,677
<i>(radio) It's 28 degrees. We'll check that</i>
<i>forecast in a minute. I feel very... weird.</i>

851
01:07:50,800 --> 01:07:54,315
<i>Very... Well,</i>
<i>the thing is I got vinyl seats in my car.</i>

852
01:07:54,440 --> 01:07:57,352
<i>When I hit the seats this morning,</i>
<i>I just went "Whoo!"</i>

853
01:07:57,480 --> 01:08:01,359
<i>I figured if I'm up, everybody</i>
<i>in the Delaware Valley should be up.</i>

854
01:08:01,480 --> 01:08:05,155
<i>Do you agree? At three minutes</i>
<i>past four, what else are you gonna do?</i>

855
01:08:05,280 --> 01:08:08,829
<i>- (ringing tone)</i>
<i>- (woman) Hello?</i>

856
01:08:08,960 --> 01:08:12,555
<i>Good morning, Mrs Kramer!</i>
<i>This is Don Cabot, WYBG Philadelphia.</i>

857
01:08:12,680 --> 01:08:15,478
<i>- How are you this morning?</i>
<i>- Huh? What?</i>

858
01:08:15,600 --> 01:08:20,754
<i>I think you have a lot of nerve callin' me</i>
<i>at this hour in the morning! Goodbye!</i>

859
01:08:20,880 --> 01:08:25,032
# <i>WYBG</i>

860
01:08:26,960 --> 01:08:31,272
# <i>Philadelphia</i>

861
01:08:32,320 --> 01:08:35,039
<i>Ha! We got Mrs Kramer up</i>
<i>and it's a good morning.</i>

862
01:08:35,160 --> 01:08:39,199
<i>Boy, I need somethin' to struggle with.</i>
<i>28 - it's cold out there.</i>

863
01:08:39,320 --> 01:08:44,394
<i>We've been getting away with murder</i>
<i>for weeks. Our high today could be 30.</i>

864
01:08:44,520 --> 01:08:48,069
<i>Tonight we're back down in the 20 range,</i>
<i>colder in the suburbs.</i>

865
01:08:48,200 --> 01:08:51,909
<i>And tomorrow, with a little bit of luck,</i>
<i>we may hit 40 somewhere.</i>

866
01:08:52,040 --> 01:08:56,511
<i>But it's awfully chilly. Make sure you</i>
<i>have it bundled up before you bring it out.</i>

867
01:11:13,080 --> 01:11:17,232
Come on. It stinks... Hey, come on!
It stinks in here, you know?

868
01:11:17,360 --> 01:11:19,316
Yeah, I know.

869
01:11:21,040 --> 01:11:23,679
Hey, do you kill all these things?

870
01:11:23,800 --> 01:11:26,155
No, across the street.

871
01:11:27,720 --> 01:11:30,393
This place looks like an animal morgue,
you know?

872
01:11:30,520 --> 01:11:33,478
- It's a little cold in here, ain't it?
- Yeah.

873
01:11:37,920 --> 01:11:40,275
Who killed all these things?

874
01:11:40,400 --> 01:11:43,790
- What, are you crazy?
- Pay Gazzo or you end up on a hook.

875
01:11:43,920 --> 01:11:46,229
Hey, Gazzo's a good man. You know that.

876
01:11:46,360 --> 01:11:51,798
Hey, don't get excited. I know that. That's
why I want you to talk to him about me.

877
01:11:51,920 --> 01:11:54,309
I can get me out of this stinkin' freezer.

878
01:11:54,440 --> 01:11:59,719
Why don't you do yourself a favour?
Keep this job, because you eat better.

879
01:11:59,840 --> 01:12:02,593
Moo... Does it ever snow in here?

880
01:12:04,080 --> 01:12:08,039
Uh, you and my sister.
How are you gettin' along together?

881
01:12:09,000 --> 01:12:10,956
How you think?

882
01:12:11,080 --> 01:12:13,913
Uh, I'm not sure, Rock. What's the story?

883
01:12:14,560 --> 01:12:18,439
- About what?
- What's the story? What's happening?

884
01:12:18,560 --> 01:12:21,518
- You really like her?
- Sure I like her.

885
01:12:23,880 --> 01:12:27,190
I don't see it. What's the attraction?

886
01:12:27,320 --> 01:12:30,630
I don't know. It fills gaps, I guess.

887
01:12:30,760 --> 01:12:34,753
- What's "gaps"?
- I don't know. She's got gaps, I got gaps.

888
01:12:34,880 --> 01:12:37,474
Together we fill gaps. I don't know...

889
01:12:38,760 --> 01:12:40,830
You ballin' her?

890
01:12:40,960 --> 01:12:42,313
Hey!

891
01:12:42,440 --> 01:12:45,398
Hey, you don't talk dirty about your sister.

892
01:12:46,800 --> 01:12:49,155
You screwin' my sister?

893
01:12:51,200 --> 01:12:54,510
You see? That's why I can't
connect you with Gazzo, Paulie.

894
01:12:54,640 --> 01:12:58,679
Because you got a big mouth, you know?
You just talk too much.

895
01:12:58,800 --> 01:13:02,873
- It's gettin' cold in here. I'm goin' home.
- Cold in here?! It <i>is</i> cold in here!

896
01:13:03,000 --> 01:13:06,197
It stinks in here! And you stink!

897
01:13:30,680 --> 01:13:32,750
<i>(cracking)</i>

898
01:13:32,880 --> 01:13:35,440
You're breakin' the ribs.

899
01:13:53,480 --> 01:13:57,632
If you do that to Apollo Creed,
they'll put us in jail for murder.

900
01:13:59,280 --> 01:14:01,840
I'll see you tomorrow mornin', OK?

901
01:14:13,760 --> 01:14:16,354
- I turned the heat up.
- Thanks.

902
01:14:16,480 --> 01:14:21,235
You know, your brother's a good man,
but he's awful pushy, you know?

903
01:14:29,880 --> 01:14:34,476
- You want me to rub you down?
- No, I'm just sore, OK? I'll just sit here.

904
01:14:34,600 --> 01:14:36,955
- You sure?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

905
01:14:40,200 --> 01:14:43,078
Hey, come on. No foolin' around, all right?

906
01:14:43,200 --> 01:14:45,077
I'm tired.

907
01:14:45,200 --> 01:14:47,156
Hey, Adrian, I'm serious now.

908
01:14:47,280 --> 01:14:51,159
There's no foolin' around durin' trainin'.
I wanna stay strong.

909
01:14:51,280 --> 01:14:54,238
- You're not kiddin'.
- No, I ain't kiddin'.

910
01:14:56,880 --> 01:14:58,711
- You sure?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

911
01:14:58,840 --> 01:15:01,434
Why don't you just make the meat, OK?

912
01:15:03,240 --> 01:15:05,390
OK, I'll make the meat.

913
01:15:28,040 --> 01:15:29,996
Yo.

914
01:15:30,720 --> 01:15:33,188
- It's OK.
- I'm sorry.

915
01:15:33,320 --> 01:15:35,276
Hey.

916
01:15:37,240 --> 01:15:39,196
Hey, c'mon.

917
01:15:40,080 --> 01:15:42,036
C'mon.

918
01:16:01,680 --> 01:16:03,750
Underneath. Underneath.

919
01:16:03,880 --> 01:16:06,599
Underneath! Underneath! Come on!

920
01:16:06,720 --> 01:16:09,188
Rock, hold it, hold it.
Hold it, Rock, will ya?

921
01:16:09,320 --> 01:16:12,869
You're drivin' me crazy,
you're so sloppy. You're off balance.

922
01:16:13,000 --> 01:16:17,790
Let's try this. Take this string. Tie it
to both ankles. Leave two feet of slack.

923
01:16:17,920 --> 01:16:21,549
- I ain't never had good footwork.
- Never mind. You're off balance.

924
01:16:21,680 --> 01:16:26,595
Marciano... He had the same problem
and this string cured it.

925
01:16:26,720 --> 01:16:30,952
The idea is that if you can move
and hit without breakin' the string...

926
01:16:31,080 --> 01:16:34,789
...you got balance. You become
a dangerous person. You follow?

927
01:16:34,920 --> 01:16:37,354
- You're lookin' good, Rock.
- Thanks.

928
01:16:37,480 --> 01:16:39,198
That's it. Underneath!

929
01:16:39,320 --> 01:16:41,709
Hey, Rock, how about an autograph?

930
01:16:41,840 --> 01:16:45,992
Get outta here! Don't you ever interrupt
me while I'm conductin' business.

931
01:16:46,120 --> 01:16:48,714
Move your little chicken asses out.

932
01:16:48,840 --> 01:16:52,628
Listen, kid. You...
You lay off that pet-shop dame.

933
01:16:52,760 --> 01:16:55,069
Women weaken legs.

934
01:16:56,320 --> 01:17:00,472
- Yeah, but I really like this girl...
- Then let her train ya!

935
01:17:03,000 --> 01:17:05,958
- OK, no more foolin' around.
- OK, now hit it.

936
01:17:08,040 --> 01:17:10,793
Women weaken legs, huh?

937
01:17:14,600 --> 01:17:16,955
- Yo, Rock!
- Yo, Rocky!

938
01:17:22,840 --> 01:17:25,115
Yo!

939
01:17:25,240 --> 01:17:27,629
- Yo!
- Yo, you look great.

940
01:17:28,760 --> 01:17:31,149
- Really?
- Oh, yeah. Terrific.

941
01:17:31,280 --> 01:17:33,555
I mean, you're gonna be a heartbreaker.

942
01:17:33,680 --> 01:17:37,514
You'll walk down the street,
breakin' hearts. Very sharp.

943
01:17:37,640 --> 01:17:40,438
- I got another surprise for you.
- What?

944
01:17:41,400 --> 01:17:45,791
Hey, Butkus! Hey, Butkus,
gimme a kiss! Come here!

945
01:17:45,920 --> 01:17:49,230
- To keep you company when you run.
<i>- (Rocky howls)</i>

946
01:17:49,360 --> 01:17:51,920
<i>(dog barks)</i>

947
01:17:53,000 --> 01:17:55,833
Come and meet the family.
The owner never come back?

948
01:17:55,960 --> 01:17:58,633
- He's yours if you want him.
- Boy, do I want him!

949
01:17:58,760 --> 01:18:01,513
- What's he eat, this dog?
- He eats little turtles.

950
01:18:01,640 --> 01:18:03,790
Yo, Butkus!

951
01:18:26,040 --> 01:18:29,715
What's that, Butkus, huh?
Whose truck is this? C'mon.

952
01:18:32,000 --> 01:18:34,560
One call from me, you're a celebrity.

953
01:18:36,440 --> 01:18:39,238
- You need exposure.
- Don't breathe on me, Paulie.

954
01:18:39,360 --> 01:18:41,920
That's the big time...
I know about these things.

955
01:18:42,040 --> 01:18:45,396
- What do these guys want from me, huh?
- To watch you train.

956
01:18:45,520 --> 01:18:48,273
Hey, what is the matter with you?
This is private.

957
01:18:48,400 --> 01:18:51,631
- I'm doin' you a favour.
- No, you're embarrassin' me...

958
01:18:51,760 --> 01:18:54,672
...in front of everybody,
in front of your sister.

959
01:18:54,800 --> 01:18:58,509
You see this cigar? Stick it in your ear.
Don't do these things to me.

960
01:18:58,640 --> 01:19:02,758
You shoulda called me up or somethin'.
Leave a message. Don't do that!

961
01:19:02,880 --> 01:19:05,235
My sister really likes you.

962
01:19:06,040 --> 01:19:09,635
- I'm gonna kill you one of these days!
- Come on, come on.

963
01:19:09,760 --> 01:19:11,716
- Pretty...
- Baby.

964
01:19:11,840 --> 01:19:16,152
Here he is, the next heavyweight
champion of the world, Rocky Balboa!

965
01:19:16,280 --> 01:19:19,397
Rocky Balboa, we wanna get
a brief interview in with you.

966
01:19:19,520 --> 01:19:20,999
- What about me?
- What about you?

967
01:19:21,120 --> 01:19:23,395
- In charge of the meat.
- Stand behind it.

968
01:19:23,520 --> 01:19:25,670
Listen, just settle down. Just relax.

969
01:19:25,800 --> 01:19:28,394
What we're going to do
is ask you a few questions...

970
01:19:28,520 --> 01:19:30,909
...about your unique training method.

971
01:19:31,040 --> 01:19:34,635
Talk to the folks at home.
They wanna know how you got into this.

972
01:19:34,760 --> 01:19:39,356
This isn't an everyday thing. Jimmy,
you guys ready? Rocky, turn around here.

973
01:19:39,480 --> 01:19:43,439
- Just don't take no cheap shots.
- No, I won't do that. Just relax.

974
01:19:43,560 --> 01:19:47,758
Today we're here with heavyweight
challenger Rocky Balboa. The reason...

975
01:19:47,880 --> 01:19:50,952
Hey, freak guy's stickin' his face in.

976
01:19:51,080 --> 01:19:52,911
Let's try it again, Rocky.

977
01:19:53,640 --> 01:19:56,712
<i>Today we're with heavyweight</i>
<i>challenger Rocky Balboa.</i>

978
01:19:56,840 --> 01:19:59,149
<i>The reason we're in this refrigerated box...</i>

979
01:19:59,280 --> 01:20:02,192
<i>... is that Mr Balboa has</i>
<i>an unusual method of training.</i>

980
01:20:02,320 --> 01:20:05,835
<i>In a moment, he's going to</i>
<i>demonstrate that for viewers at home.</i>

981
01:20:05,960 --> 01:20:09,714
<i>But first, Rocky,</i>
<i>how did you come to train in an icebox?</i>

982
01:20:09,840 --> 01:20:13,116
<i>Uh, well, my friend,</i>
<i>the guy over there, he let me in one day.</i>

983
01:20:13,240 --> 01:20:15,196
<i>I hit the beef and I kinda liked it.</i>

984
01:20:15,320 --> 01:20:18,710
<i>Since I've become a challenger,</i>
<i>the owner don't mind neither.</i>

985
01:20:18,840 --> 01:20:22,753
<i>Is this a common training method?</i>
<i>Do other fighters pound raw meat?</i>

986
01:20:22,880 --> 01:20:27,829
<i>- No, I think I invented it.</i>
<i>- Would you give us a demonstration?</i>

987
01:20:27,960 --> 01:20:31,316
<i>(Apollo)</i> And be sure
to fly my barber to Philly.

988
01:20:34,120 --> 01:20:36,680
How much is going to
West Coast advertising?

989
01:20:36,800 --> 01:20:39,030
- $300,000.
- Make it 450.

990
01:20:39,160 --> 01:20:41,196
Send the mayor's wife 200 roses...

991
01:20:41,320 --> 01:20:44,118
...and make sure we get
a picture for the newspapers.

992
01:20:44,240 --> 01:20:47,038
Do you want to run
15 radio spots in the Midwest?

993
01:20:47,160 --> 01:20:49,720
You could spend better
in Canadian publicity.

994
01:20:49,840 --> 01:20:54,789
Either way, I've got friends in Toronto
who could get you good tax breaks.

995
01:20:54,920 --> 01:20:57,275
George, I like your friends.

996
01:21:03,880 --> 01:21:08,908
Hey, champ, you oughta come and look
at this boy you're gonna fight on TV.

997
01:21:09,040 --> 01:21:12,191
- Looks like he means business.
- Yeah, I mean business too.

998
01:21:12,320 --> 01:21:17,474
- Hey, Shirley, we got any more coffee?
- Certainly, Mr Creed. I'll get you some.

999
01:21:33,800 --> 01:21:38,351
<i>Diana Lewis, in the meat house,</i>
<i>with southpaw Rocky Balboa.</i>

1000
01:21:41,160 --> 01:21:43,720
<i>(</i># <i>drunkenly hums "The First Noel")</i>

1001
01:22:23,360 --> 01:22:27,433
- <i>(Adrian)</i> He called the reporters?
- <i>(Rocky)</i> It threw my trainin' schedule off.

1002
01:22:27,560 --> 01:22:29,915
Don't be mad at him. He's tryin' to help.

1003
01:22:30,040 --> 01:22:34,830
Adrian, I ain't mad. It's just that when
reporters are around, I get out of joint.

1004
01:22:34,960 --> 01:22:37,838
They take cheap shots. Paulie knows that.

1005
01:22:37,960 --> 01:22:40,997
Paulie keeps askin' me
for a job all the time...

1006
01:22:41,120 --> 01:22:43,839
...but he don't know nothin' about fightin'.

1007
01:22:43,960 --> 01:22:46,952
Are you gonna say anything to him?

1008
01:22:47,080 --> 01:22:50,834
What's to say?
I just don't know what he wants from me.

1009
01:22:52,640 --> 01:22:55,154
I don't want nothin' from you.

1010
01:22:55,400 --> 01:22:58,278
I don't want nothin' from you.

1011
01:22:58,400 --> 01:23:02,075
This ain't no charity case.
Get outta my house!

1012
01:23:02,200 --> 01:23:04,794
It's not just <i>your</i> house.

1013
01:23:04,920 --> 01:23:08,754
He's no friend no more.
Get outta my house, I just said.

1014
01:23:08,880 --> 01:23:12,873
- Don't talk to him like that.
- Both of ya, get outta my house!

1015
01:23:13,000 --> 01:23:16,549
Yo... it's cold outside, Paulie.

1016
01:23:26,080 --> 01:23:28,036
I don't want ya messin' her.

1017
01:23:28,160 --> 01:23:30,515
I don't raise ya to go with this scumball!

1018
01:23:30,640 --> 01:23:32,995
Yeah?! C'mon!
You wanna hit on me? C'mon!

1019
01:23:33,120 --> 01:23:37,238
I'll break both your arms,
so they don't work for ya!

1020
01:23:39,040 --> 01:23:42,919
I'm not good enough to meet with Gazzo?
That's what I think of Gazzo!

1021
01:23:43,040 --> 01:23:47,158
Now you're a big-shot fighter on your way
up, you don't even throw me a crumb!

1022
01:23:47,280 --> 01:23:51,751
When I go and get you meat every
mornin'! I even give you my sister, too!

1023
01:23:51,880 --> 01:23:55,156
- Only a pig would say that!
- I'm a pig?

1024
01:23:55,280 --> 01:23:57,669
A pig gets you the best?

1025
01:23:57,800 --> 01:24:01,236
I'm a loser!
I don't get married because of you!

1026
01:24:01,560 --> 01:24:03,630
You can't live by yourself!

1027
01:24:03,760 --> 01:24:08,197
I put you two together, and you...
don't you ever forget it! You owe me!

1028
01:24:11,080 --> 01:24:13,071
- You owe me!
- What do I owe you?

1029
01:24:13,200 --> 01:24:15,509
You're supposed to be good to me.

1030
01:24:15,640 --> 01:24:19,030
What do I owe you, Paulie?
What do I owe ya?

1031
01:24:19,160 --> 01:24:23,676
I treat you good. I cook for you, I clean
for you, I pick up your dirty clothes!

1032
01:24:23,800 --> 01:24:27,759
I take care of you, Paulie!
I don't owe you nothin'!

1033
01:24:27,880 --> 01:24:32,829
And you made me feel like
a loser! I'm not a loser!

1034
01:24:32,960 --> 01:24:35,235
- You're busted!
- What?!

1035
01:24:35,360 --> 01:24:39,035
You're not a virgin!
You let a man take down your pants!

1036
01:24:39,160 --> 01:24:41,993
She's busted! <i>(whimpers)</i>

1037
01:24:43,760 --> 01:24:46,718
I can't haul meat no more.

1038
01:25:15,080 --> 01:25:17,640
You want a roommate?

1039
01:25:21,440 --> 01:25:24,079
Absolutely.

1040
01:25:24,360 --> 01:25:29,309
OK, now when you walk into the ring
with the No.1 heavyweight of the world...

1041
01:25:29,440 --> 01:25:31,749
...you'll be ready, won't ya? Why?

1042
01:25:31,880 --> 01:25:35,953
Because I've waited
for 50 years to make ya ready.

1043
01:25:36,080 --> 01:25:38,514
You'll be able to spit nails, kid.

1044
01:25:38,640 --> 01:25:42,838
Like the guy says, you're gonna eat
lightning and you're gonna crap thunder!

1045
01:25:42,960 --> 01:25:45,793
You're gonna become
a very dangerous person.

1046
01:25:45,920 --> 01:25:48,832
- Yo, Mickey!
- Hey! Oh, Rock.

1047
01:25:48,960 --> 01:25:51,952
I want ya to meet our cut man here,
Al Salvani.

1048
01:25:52,080 --> 01:25:54,833
- Take a look at his eye, kid.
- How you doin', Al?

1049
01:25:54,960 --> 01:25:57,793
- Not bad. I've seen worse.
- You ain't so bad yourself.

1050
01:25:57,920 --> 01:26:00,593
- Cover up. Things'll be OK.
- <i>You</i> cover up.

1051
01:26:00,720 --> 01:26:05,350
- Go and take a shower, will ya?
- OK, Mick. I'll see ya's tomorrow.

1052
01:26:05,480 --> 01:26:09,234
- Hey, you covered that Whitmore fight.
- That's why he won.

1053
01:26:09,360 --> 01:26:12,113
Listen, we got a winner here.
We got a chance.

1054
01:26:12,240 --> 01:26:15,198
He goes to the body
like nobody you've ever seen.

1055
01:26:15,320 --> 01:26:18,278
You just stand by for him.
We're gonna win.

1056
01:26:24,600 --> 01:26:27,160
Hey, Rocky. It's OK I talk to ya?

1057
01:26:27,880 --> 01:26:30,235
OK you talk to me? Sure.

1058
01:26:31,240 --> 01:26:33,708
I figured an angle
to make money off your name.

1059
01:26:33,840 --> 01:26:36,479
My name? How's that?

1060
01:26:36,600 --> 01:26:39,353
Advertising. I know about that stuff.

1061
01:26:41,000 --> 01:26:43,958
What do you know about advertising?
Huh?

1062
01:26:46,520 --> 01:26:51,275
Hey, you can make money off my name,
make it, OK? I'm gonna take a shower.

1063
01:26:52,120 --> 01:26:54,509
- Hey, wanna help me off with these?
- Sure.

1064
