Apollo?

1086
01:33:16,800 --> 01:33:19,075
Yeah.

1087
01:33:19,200 --> 01:33:22,158
I been out there, walking around, thinkin'.

1088
01:33:23,840 --> 01:33:27,799
I mean, who am I kiddin'?
I ain't even in the guy's league.

1089
01:33:32,080 --> 01:33:34,036
What are we gonna do?

1090
01:33:44,880 --> 01:33:46,836
I don't know.

1091
01:33:52,400 --> 01:33:54,755
You worked so hard.

1092
01:33:55,880 --> 01:33:59,236
Yeah, it don't matter,
cos I was nobody before.

1093
01:34:01,240 --> 01:34:03,390
Don't say that.

1094
01:34:03,520 --> 01:34:06,876
Come on, Adrian. It's true. I was nobody.

1095
01:34:09,040 --> 01:34:11,600
But that don't matter either, you know?

1096
01:34:12,600 --> 01:34:14,750
Cos I was thinkin'...

1097
01:34:15,600 --> 01:34:18,558
It really don't matter if I lose this fight.

1098
01:34:20,200 --> 01:34:24,159
It really don't matter if this guy
opens my head either.

1099
01:34:25,200 --> 01:34:28,158
Cos all I wanna do is go the distance.

1100
01:34:32,280 --> 01:34:35,875
Nobody's ever
gone the distance with Creed.

1101
01:34:36,000 --> 01:34:38,355
And if I can go that distance...

1102
01:34:39,400 --> 01:34:42,756
...and that bell rings and I'm still standin'...

1103
01:34:47,520 --> 01:34:51,069
...l'm gonna know for
the first time in my life, see...

1104
01:34:52,640 --> 01:34:56,599
...that I weren't just another
bum from the neighbourhood.

1105
01:36:00,240 --> 01:36:02,390
Time, kid. Let's go.

1106
01:36:05,000 --> 01:36:07,355
I'll wait for you here.

1107
01:36:09,080 --> 01:36:12,470
Well, how about I wait here and you fight,
you know?

1108
01:36:12,600 --> 01:36:15,956
You're lookin' very great today.
You know that? Mm?

1109
01:36:17,520 --> 01:36:20,478
I gotta go now,
but don't you leave town, huh?

1110
01:36:21,800 --> 01:36:24,712
Wish me luck. I'm gonna need it.

1111
01:36:24,840 --> 01:36:26,717
Good luck.

1112
01:36:26,840 --> 01:36:30,196
Say, Adrian, you don't think
this robe is too baggy, you know?

1113
01:36:30,320 --> 01:36:33,232
- Good luck.
- Don't leave town.

1114
01:36:35,360 --> 01:36:38,830
I'd like you to meet the man
working the fight with me, Stu Nahan.

1115
01:36:38,960 --> 01:36:42,999
Thank you, Bill Baldwin. The electricity
is all over the place tonight...

1116
01:36:44,840 --> 01:36:48,594
What the hell is that? I trained you
to be a fighter, not a billboard.

1117
01:36:48,720 --> 01:36:51,473
- I'm doin' it for a friend.
- What do you get out of it?

1118
01:36:51,600 --> 01:36:55,149
- Paulie gets three grand, I get the robe.
- Shrewd.

1119
01:36:55,280 --> 01:36:57,999
On tonight's fight,
their difference in style...

1120
01:36:58,120 --> 01:37:01,874
...a recent magazine said it could be
the caveman against the cavalier.

1121
01:37:02,000 --> 01:37:06,437
The buzzing in the background could be
the challenger getting into the ring.

1122
01:37:06,560 --> 01:37:12,351
- Rocky! Look at me! Ya cost me $200.
- Oh. I gotta go. I gotta work.

1123
01:37:12,480 --> 01:37:14,675
- How's the robe?
- A little baggy.

1124
01:37:14,800 --> 01:37:17,678
<i>(Bill)</i> A 50-1 underdog,
a Cinderella story...

1125
01:37:17,800 --> 01:37:21,679
...and he's captured people's
imaginations all over the world.

1126
01:37:25,640 --> 01:37:27,835
We love you, Rocky!

1127
01:37:27,960 --> 01:37:30,554
- Yo, champ!
- Hey, thanks for showin' up.

1128
01:37:30,680 --> 01:37:35,037
<i>(Stu)</i> His record: 44 victories -
38 by knockout. And he's lost 20 fights.

1129
01:37:35,160 --> 01:37:37,594
<i>(Bill)</i> Which makes me wonder,
can he stand it?

1130
01:37:37,720 --> 01:37:42,032
The stamina and the skill to last
the three rounds? Las Vegas odds say no.

1131
01:37:42,160 --> 01:37:45,470
Rocky Balboa climbing into the ring now.

1132
01:37:45,600 --> 01:37:50,435
The Italian Stallion. Some meat sign
on the back of his robe there. See that?

1133
01:37:50,560 --> 01:37:52,710
"Shamrock Meat Company."

1134
01:37:52,840 --> 01:37:56,913
<i>(Stu)</i> There's a lot of noise.
You could go deaf with that noise!

1135
01:37:57,040 --> 01:37:59,235
Am I seeing right back there?

1136
01:37:59,360 --> 01:38:02,397
Is that the world heavyweight champion,
Apollo Creed?

1137
01:38:02,520 --> 01:38:06,479
<i>(Bill)</i> He's riding in a boat. Is he
supposed to be George Washington?

1138
01:38:06,600 --> 01:38:09,239
Obviously so.
He's got the hat on. Look at that.

1139
01:38:09,360 --> 01:38:13,114
<i>(Stu)</i> Well, it's been confirmed.
The world champion Apollo Creed...

1140
01:38:13,240 --> 01:38:16,391
<i>... is</i> doing an imitation
of George Washington.

1141
01:38:17,480 --> 01:38:19,152
He's throwing money.

1142
01:38:19,280 --> 01:38:23,319
Remember when we talked about
George Washington throwing a dollar?

1143
01:38:23,440 --> 01:38:28,036
Of course, throwing a dollar
in those days went a lot farther.

1144
01:38:28,160 --> 01:38:31,118
The white wig came off,
the hat came off...

1145
01:38:32,040 --> 01:38:34,508
I want all of you!

1146
01:38:34,640 --> 01:38:39,760
And the crowd is loving every minute of it.
Here is the world heavyweight champion.

1147
01:38:39,880 --> 01:38:44,192
<i>(Bill)</i> For you around the world,
he was dressed as George Washington.

1148
01:38:44,320 --> 01:38:47,278
I want all of you! Come on, Stallion!

1149
01:38:50,560 --> 01:38:53,279
- <i>(Stu)</i> Uncle Sam himself...
- I want all of you!

1150
01:38:53,400 --> 01:38:58,315
- All of you! I want all of you!
- He looks like a big flag.

1151
01:38:58,440 --> 01:39:00,829
I want you! You!

1152
01:39:01,600 --> 01:39:03,511
- Is he talkin' to me?
- He is.

1153
01:39:03,640 --> 01:39:05,756
- Is he talkin' to me?
- Let him talk.

1154
01:39:05,880 --> 01:39:08,269
I want the Stallion! Come on!

1155
01:39:08,400 --> 01:39:11,153
<i>(Bill)</i> He says "I want the Stallion!"

1156
01:39:12,000 --> 01:39:15,993
In foreign countries during World War I
there was a picture of Uncle Sam...

1157
01:39:16,120 --> 01:39:17,951
...with his finger pointed -

1158
01:39:18,080 --> 01:39:22,358
...a recruiting poster for our fellows
in the army and the navy. "I want you!"

1159
01:39:22,480 --> 01:39:24,436
<i>(Stu)</i> That's what he's doing a take on.

1160
01:39:24,560 --> 01:39:27,358
- That's it. "Creed" he's yelling.
- "Creed in three."

1161
01:39:27,480 --> 01:39:29,755
What do you think that outfit cost?

1162
01:39:29,880 --> 01:39:32,030
<i>(fanfare)</i>

1163
01:39:35,000 --> 01:39:37,150
<i>(bell)</i>

1164
01:39:39,640 --> 01:39:42,473
Ladies and gentlemen...

1165
01:39:42,600 --> 01:39:46,229
...good evening. A very happy new year.

1166
01:39:46,360 --> 01:39:48,316
Welcome to Philadelphia.

1167
01:39:48,440 --> 01:39:51,398
<i>(Stu)</i> Everybody who's anybody
is here tonight.

1168
01:39:53,040 --> 01:39:59,513
Time does not permit me to introduce
the many luminaries of politics...

1169
01:39:59,640 --> 01:40:03,792
...show business and the sporting world
who are with us tonight.

1170
01:40:04,400 --> 01:40:09,269
But I would like to present
one of the immortals of pugilism...

1171
01:40:09,400 --> 01:40:12,790
...a champion in and out of the ring.

1172
01:40:12,920 --> 01:40:15,480
Philadelphia's own Smokin' Joe...

1173
01:40:15,600 --> 01:40:18,592
...the beloved Mr Joe Frazier!

1174
01:40:18,720 --> 01:40:21,280
<i>(cheering, whistling and applause)</i>

1175
01:40:28,400 --> 01:40:31,949
Hi, how are you doing?
Don't hurt him, OK?

1176
01:40:32,080 --> 01:40:35,197
<i>(Stu)</i> What a credit he's been
in his career as a fighter.

1177
01:40:35,320 --> 01:40:37,436
He's coming over to talk with the champ.

1178
01:40:37,560 --> 01:40:40,472
- Hey, Joe!
- You been dumpin' me long time.

1179
01:40:40,600 --> 01:40:43,353
You next, Joe! You next, Joe!

1180
01:40:44,440 --> 01:40:46,749
They must be friends.

1181
01:40:54,080 --> 01:40:55,832
Joe Frazier!

1182
01:40:55,960 --> 01:41:00,431
Fight fans around the world, get settled
down, because it won't be long now.

1183
01:41:00,560 --> 01:41:01,879
<i>(bell)</i>

1184
01:41:02,000 --> 01:41:05,709
And now... for the main event!

1185
01:41:09,160 --> 01:41:11,754
On my left, the challenger.

1186
01:41:12,760 --> 01:41:16,958
In white trunks, weighing 190lb...

1187
01:41:17,080 --> 01:41:19,833
...Philadelphia's favourite son...

1188
01:41:19,960 --> 01:41:24,476
...the Italian Stallion, Rocky Balboa!

1189
01:41:24,600 --> 01:41:27,160
<i>(cheering and some booing)</i>

1190
01:41:30,960 --> 01:41:35,476
And on my right,
wearing red, white and blue...

1191
01:41:35,600 --> 01:41:38,637
...weighing 210lb...

1192
01:41:38,960 --> 01:41:42,032
...undefeated in 46 fights...

1193
01:41:42,440 --> 01:41:44,954
...the Master of Disaster...

1194
01:41:45,080 --> 01:41:48,516
...the undisputed
heavyweight champion of the world...

1195
01:41:48,800 --> 01:41:52,509
...Apollo Creed!
<i>- (cheering)</i>

1196
01:41:52,640 --> 01:41:55,029
I want you! I want you!

1197
01:41:57,640 --> 01:41:59,835
You, chump! I want you!

1198
01:41:59,960 --> 01:42:02,235
You've both fought in Philadelphia before.

1199
01:42:02,360 --> 01:42:06,114
You know the rules. No low blows.
Watch your heads. No buttin'.

1200
01:42:06,240 --> 01:42:11,189
- Shake hands now and come out fightin'.
- Put your hands up, chump. Come on!

1201
01:42:11,320 --> 01:42:15,598
<i>(Bill)</i> A little body play goin' on there.
Rocky taking it carefully, though.

1202
01:42:15,720 --> 01:42:19,349
He's just going over and being calm,
it looks like from here.

1203
01:42:19,480 --> 01:42:21,914
There goes the big hat.

1204
01:42:24,240 --> 01:42:28,313
<i>(Stu)</i> I've never seen a fighter
that concerned about his hair!

1205
01:42:36,000 --> 01:42:39,037
And there's the bell for round one.

1206
01:42:39,160 --> 01:42:43,358
The fighters come out into the centre
of the ring, looking at each other.

1207
01:42:43,480 --> 01:42:48,235
Creed the champion zipping those
left-handed jabs, right in the head.

1208
01:42:50,360 --> 01:42:53,511
The champ stinging
the slower challenger jabs at will.

1209
01:42:53,640 --> 01:42:57,474
In fact, it looks like Rocky is
blocking the blows with his face.

1210
01:42:57,600 --> 01:43:01,832
The champion doesn't look the best
he's ever been, but he's moving smoothly.

1211
01:43:01,960 --> 01:43:05,748
Well, the champion is smiling now.
He's toying with his man.

1212
01:43:05,880 --> 01:43:10,396
Tryin' to give the fans their money's
worth. He's makin' a show of it.

1213
01:43:10,520 --> 01:43:13,876
And a very badly outclassed
challenger right now.

1214
01:43:16,040 --> 01:43:18,110
<i>(Bill)</i> Creed trying to
make this man make...

1215
01:43:18,240 --> 01:43:21,038
See? Make him miss like that.

1216
01:43:21,160 --> 01:43:23,799
<i>(Stu)</i> Oh, the champ
is just taunting him now.

1217
01:43:26,720 --> 01:43:29,075
Creed dancing around.

1218
01:43:30,000 --> 01:43:32,389
I don't believe it! The champ is down!

1219
01:43:32,520 --> 01:43:34,476
<i>(Bill)</i> Yes, he is!

1220
01:43:39,560 --> 01:43:42,597
Creed is down! What a surprise this is!

1221
01:43:43,880 --> 01:43:47,998
<i>(Stu)</i> This is the first time the champion
has ever been knocked down.

1222
01:43:49,320 --> 01:43:51,709
Six! Seven! Eight!

1223
01:43:51,840 --> 01:43:54,877
He appears to be all right.
Glancin' around...

1224
01:43:55,240 --> 01:43:59,472
<i>(Mickey)</i> Come on, Rock! Go to the ribs!
Let's go to work right now, Rock!

1225
01:44:00,960 --> 01:44:05,112
<i>(Bill)</i> Rocky comes back out. He's like
a bull in a china closet. He really wants it.

1226
01:44:05,240 --> 01:44:07,754
Apollo, left to the head.

1227
01:44:07,880 --> 01:44:12,158
<i>(Stu)</i> Now the champion's comin' back.
He's comin' off the floor now.

1228
01:44:13,000 --> 01:44:18,518
<i>(Bill)</i> Another left, another right.
Combinations into the face. That's Apollo!

1229
01:44:21,480 --> 01:44:24,756
Now the champ is taunting Rocky
to come and get some more.

1230
01:44:24,880 --> 01:44:26,791
Left. Another.

1231
01:44:26,920 --> 01:44:28,956
Another left!

1232
01:44:29,920 --> 01:44:32,275
And Rocky's coming back now!

1233
01:44:33,040 --> 01:44:35,793
Left! Right! Rocky's got him on the rope!

1234
01:44:36,560 --> 01:44:38,710
OK, let's break it.

1235
01:44:43,000 --> 01:44:46,549
There's no way they expected
this kind of hitting power.

1236
01:44:46,680 --> 01:44:50,878
But the ability of the champion,
Apollo, is apparent.

1237
01:44:52,920 --> 01:44:57,232
<i>(Stu)</i> Apollo unloading,
Rocky really tight against the ropes.

1238
01:44:57,360 --> 01:44:59,316
<i>(bell)</i>

1239
01:45:03,880 --> 01:45:08,317
They're leading him back over to his
corner. Rocky can hardly find his way.

1240
01:45:08,440 --> 01:45:11,398
- I told ya! I told ya!
- Your nose is broke.

1241
01:45:11,520 --> 01:45:13,715
- How does it look?
- It's an improvement.

1242
01:45:13,840 --> 01:45:16,991
I want you to quit chuckin' and jivin'.
Stick and move.

1243
01:45:17,120 --> 01:45:18,633
Go for the ribs.

1244
01:45:18,760 --> 01:45:22,275
- Don't let that bastard breathe.
- The guy's great.

1245
01:45:22,400 --> 01:45:25,870
He doesn't know it's a damn show.
He thinks it's a damn fight.

1246
01:45:26,000 --> 01:45:28,753
- Finish this bum and let's go home.
- Right.

1247
01:45:29,320 --> 01:45:31,470
Stay to the body! To his right!

1248
01:45:31,600 --> 01:45:34,956
<i>(Stu)</i> Here we go. Round two.
Creed predicted he would win in three.

1249
01:45:35,080 --> 01:45:38,550
Creed got knocked down in the first.
He came back at the end.

1250
01:45:38,680 --> 01:45:40,671
<i>(Bill)</i> Oh, he's working now.

1251
01:45:40,800 --> 01:45:43,189
Oh, that sharp left! Again, a hard right.

1252
01:45:43,320 --> 01:45:45,754
He's working Rocky into the corner again.

1253
01:45:45,880 --> 01:45:47,836
He's got Rocky back in the corner.

1254
01:45:47,960 --> 01:45:52,317
Pelting him left and right.
He's bouncing up against the ring.

1255
01:45:52,880 --> 01:45:55,713
<i>(Stu)</i> Oh, Balboa's taking
a tremendous beating here.

1256
01:45:55,840 --> 01:46:00,356
- <i>(Bill)</i> Battering him like a punching bag.
- <i>(Stu)</i> What's keeping him up?

1257
01:46:07,240 --> 01:46:09,674
- He says he wants more!
- <i>(Bill)</i> He wants more!

1258
01:46:09,800 --> 01:46:14,157
You folks in front of your television
are watching a battle, I tell you that!

1259
01:46:17,840 --> 01:46:21,515
<i>(Stu)</i> Balboa trying to fight back...
Ooh, a tremendous hook!

1260
01:46:21,640 --> 01:46:24,916
<i>(Bill)</i> The champion is trying
to get himself out, but he can't.

1261
01:46:25,040 --> 01:46:28,396
He is being barraged
with lefts and rights to his body!

1262
01:46:28,520 --> 01:46:31,990
<i>(Stu)</i> Balboa is smacking the champion
right on the kisser!

1263
01:46:32,120 --> 01:46:34,350
<i>- (bell)</i>
- The referee's stepped in.

1264
01:46:34,480 --> 01:46:36,710
They're ready to keep going!

1265
01:46:36,840 --> 01:46:38,956
Back to your corner!

1266
01:46:39,080 --> 01:46:41,355
Come on, Creed!

1267
01:46:41,720 --> 01:46:43,790
<i>(Stu)</i> This is gonna be a tough one.

1268
01:47:47,680 --> 01:47:49,636
<i>(Bill)</i> Hard left and right combination!

1269
01:47:49,760 --> 01:47:52,718
<i>(Stu)</i> What is keeping him up, Bill?
I don't know!

1270
01:47:54,920 --> 01:47:58,276
He can't even get his gloves up
to protect himself!

1271
01:48:04,680 --> 01:48:06,716
Down! Down! Stay down!

1272
01:48:06,840 --> 01:48:09,991
<i>(Bill)</i> Apollo dancing around
with his arms in the air!

1273
01:48:19,520 --> 01:48:21,715
Five!

1274
01:48:21,840 --> 01:48:24,195
Six! Seven!

1275
01:48:24,880 --> 01:48:26,950
Eight! Nine!

1276
01:48:32,000 --> 01:48:34,355
OK, OK. Come on!

1277
01:48:36,400 --> 01:48:38,994
<i>(Bill)</i> Apollo can't believe it!

1278
01:48:51,320 --> 01:48:53,276
<i>(bell)</i>

1279
01:48:53,960 --> 01:48:57,748
<i>(Stu)</i> The champion got a left to the ribs,
his right ribs.

1280
01:49:05,440 --> 01:49:08,193
- You OK, champ?
- Yeah, I'm OK, I'm OK.

1281
01:49:10,520 --> 01:49:13,796
I can't see nothin'.
I gotta open my eye. Cut me, Mick.

1282
01:49:13,920 --> 01:49:17,276
- You don't wanna do it.
- Go on, cut me. Cut me.

1283
01:49:24,400 --> 01:49:30,032
- You're bleeding inside. I'm gonna stop it.
- You ain't stoppin' nothin', man.

1284
01:49:30,480 --> 01:49:32,835
You stop this fight, I'll kill ya.

1285
01:49:39,000 --> 01:49:40,956
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Rocky!

1286
01:49:46,760 --> 01:49:48,352
<i>(Bill) The 15th and final round.</i>

1287
01:49:49,520 --> 01:49:53,798
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!

1288
01:49:57,040 --> 01:49:59,998
<i>(Stu)</i> They look like they've
been in a war, these two.

1289
01:50:08,160 --> 01:50:10,435
<i>(Bill)</i> The champion really tightening!

1290
01:50:10,560 --> 01:50:14,314
And Apollo clearly protecting
his right side, his ribs.

1291
01:50:19,240 --> 01:50:22,152
<i>(Stu)</i> Hard left and right!
Look at the blood coming out!

1292
01:50:22,280 --> 01:50:25,511
<i>(Bill)</i> Oh, he's spitting out blood now.

1293
01:50:27,560 --> 01:50:30,233
A tremendous right hand from Rocky!

1294
01:50:30,360 --> 01:50:32,157
Go for it, Rock!

1295
01:50:32,280 --> 01:50:35,033
- <i>(Bill)</i> Listen to this crowd!
- <i>(Stu)</i> Left to the ribs.

1296
01:50:37,360 --> 01:50:41,035
Right to the chin!
He's got him up against the rope!

1297
01:50:41,760 --> 01:50:43,159
<i>(bell)</i>

1298
01:50:45,440 --> 01:50:48,637
<i>(Apollo)</i> There ain't gonna be no rematch!

1299
01:50:48,760 --> 01:50:50,239
<i>(Rocky)</i> Don't want one.

1300
01:51:00,080 --> 01:51:02,469
Rocky, you went the distance, 15 rounds.

1301
01:51:02,600 --> 01:51:05,637
- How do you feel?
- All right. It's all right.

1302
01:51:05,760 --> 01:51:09,594
- Adrian! Adrian!
- What did you think in the 15th round...

1303
01:51:09,720 --> 01:51:13,395
- Rocky! Rocky!
- <i>(MC)</i> Ladies and gentlemen...

1304
01:51:13,520 --> 01:51:16,592
